dparser
Class Parser

java.lang.Object
  dparser.Parser

public class Parser
extends Object

Parser written for the CalSol datalogger This is the actual class that does the hard work of interpreting the datalogger signals. It deciphers the datalogger opCode first and then interprets the payload.

Since:
2012.05.13
Version:
1.00
Author:
Derek Chou

Method Detail

parse

public void parse(String data)
Parses the datalogger output into more intelligible things. Where the data goes or which ArrayList it's added into is dependent on its opCode and payload. This method currently ignores PRM/PWM messages.

Parameters:
data - A line of datalogger output.

decodeJSON

private ArrayList<String> decodeJSON(String[] sp)
Decodes a CAN Message using JSON libraries. This method implements some pre-made JSON decoders, imported. This triple for loop is there because someone decided to put values inside values for the JSON files.

Parameters:
sp - The payload incoming from a CAN Message.
